"Where's my leg, Mom?" The words are of a four-year-old Palestinian child in Egypt, Cairo. To bring them back to the Chamber is Angelo Bonelli, Member of the Green and Left Alliance. Bonelli together with a delegation of parliamentarians, a month ago he went to the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-27/raid-israele-a-rafah-26548051/">valico of Rafah</a> to sincerely state of sending humanitarian aid and, on that occasion he visited the Egyptian nosocomium. "It is a horror and it is not possible to have the unawareness of a government that has no courage to tell Israel 'just enough'. The State of Palestine must be recognized and sanctions are made to Israel because it can no longer commit these crimes against humanity." An appeal that turns into a choir in the classroom. First Norway and Spain, then Ireland. The recognition of the State of Palestine by the three European countries is now official. And in this wake, the pressing of oppositions to the government grows because Italy also recognizes the Palestinian state.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
In Classroom the request of Green Alliance and Left, Movement 5 Stars and Democratic Party sounds like a single voice. The 5 Star Movement formalized the request with an ad hoc motion in which the government's commitment to work to recognize the State of Palestine within the 1967 borders. "We have tabled a motion for the recognition of the State of Palestine and we ask that the government and the President of the Council be in the Chamber to take responsibility for once," says M5s Vice President Riccardo Ricciardi, taking the floor between Palestinian flags and the peace waved by his party colleagues.&nbsp;<span> "Too easy to declare and then not vote". Too easy to declare and then do not take the solemnity of a vote a position," adds the Five Stars. </span
&nbsp;
<span>Poco had previously been MP and Foreign Manager of the Pd, Peppe Provenzano, to urge the government and the President of the Council. "I come back to ask in this House an urgent statement to Meloni and Tajani on what initiatives we are taking as Italy. I do this with an increasing anguish, after last night's attacks in Rafah, with children burned alive by the death coming from the sky", emphasizes the exponent dem that, then, dwells on the recognition of the State of Palestine arrived from 143 countries in the world, from last the three European countries: "We express a great appreciation to Spain, Norway and Ireland for an act that serves to preserve the prospect of the two nations. It is time for Italy to join in honoring a commitment that this Parliament had assumed in 2015". Words that Provenzano accompanies with a parallelism between what Italian children live in these days and what they are forced to endure their Palestinian peers. "These are special days: schools end, many of us attend the end of the year, we get pictures of those happy children. In the same moments, we cannot divert our gaze from those images of hatred, destruction of life, those massacres of innocents coming from there. These are images that will pursue us for decades if we do not find the strength to react." </span
